{{Multiple issues|{{orphan|date=February 2014}}{{primary sources|date=February 2014}}{{one source|date=February 2014}}}}
[[File:EBCD logo.png|right|thumb]] The '''European Bureau for Conservation and Development''' (EBCD) is an environmentally focused [[w:non governmental organisation|non governmental organisation]] (NGO) founded in 1989 and based in [[w:Brussels|Brussels]], [[w:Belgium|Belgium]].<ref>http://www.ebcd.org/en/About/</ref> EBCD aims to promote sustainable use of natural renewable resources not just in Europe, but worldwide as well. The EBCD works closely with the [[w:European Union|European Union]] (EU) institutions, tracking EU work on environmental policy, concentrating on fisheries and marine policies.
EBCD provides, in association with the [[w:International Union for Conservation of Nature|International Union for Conservation of Nature]], the Secretariat of the European Parliament Intergroup: “Climate Change, Biodiversity and Sustainable Development”.<ref>http://www.ebcd.org/en/EP_Intergroup_CCBSD/</ref>
EBCD's mission: to ensure the conservation and sustainable use of natural renewable resources including species and ecosystems both for their intrinsic and direct value to the benefit of humanity <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ebcd.org/ebcd/our-work/|title=Our work - EBCD|language=en-US|access-date=2016-09-26}}</ref>
== Main Activities == * Secretariat of the [http://ebcd.org/intergroup/ European Parliament Intergroup] on “Climate Change, Biodiversity and Sustainable Development” * Secretariat of the IUCN European Sustainable Use Specialist Group (ESUSG) and the coordination of Fisheries Working Group (FWG) * Secretariat of the [http://ebcd.org/feg/ Fisheries Experts Group] of the IUCN/CEM/FEG *
